ref: Jour: Nuclear Physics, Section A, Vol.226, p.413 (1974)
title: Level densities of 63Cu and 65Cu from the analysis of evaporation spectra

x4freetext: Level densities of 63Cu and 65Cu from the analysis of
evaporation spectra

x4codes.hlp: Purdue University, West Lafayette, IN, United States of America

x4codes.shortRef: Jour: Nuclear Physics, Section A, Vol.226, p.413 (1974)

x4codes.hlp: Purdue University, West Lafayette, IN, United States of America

x4freetext: A counter telescope consisting of two
surface-barrier detectors.
Targets were self-supporting foils of highly enriched
60Ni, 62Ni, 63Cu, 65Cu, 66Zn, and 68Zn. The surface
density of the targets varied between 0.71 and 0.98
mg/cm2, as determined by energy loss measurements
performed with an 241Am alpha source.
63,65Cu deduced level density, pairing energy
parameters from comparison with spin-,
isospin-dependent statistical theory.
OG
No information on uncertainties.
